ACTION:
With power OFF and all modules accessible, use a multimeter in diode/ohms mode on the load module only. (1) Test the series protection diode: measure between the input terminal (from control +) and the diode output node going to the lamps, first one polarity then reversed. Confirm it conducts in only one direction and note the forward drop; check for an open circuit in both directions which would indicate an open diode or a break in the PCB trace. (2) From the diode output node, check continuity to each side of both lamps and then through each lamp to the return terminal (from control −). This will reveal any open trace, bad joint, or open filament that is not visible. Record which segment, if any, is open or has abnormal resistance.
