h relative to the control module’s 0 V rail: the branch is tied into the wrong internal node so that it is forward‑biased in normal operation, stealing current and preventing proper operation of the load. Correcting this wiring to match the intended schematic (LED/resistor strictly between the two incoming lines, reverse‑biased for correct polarity) will eliminate the spurious LED conduction and allow full voltage and current to be delivered to the lamps, restoring system operation.'
